For this reason,

290
00:17:36,360 --> 00:17:38,080
the county's top leaders called

291
00:17:38,680 --> 00:17:40,360
to give this Paper King Competition

292
00:17:40,520 --> 00:17:43,240
strong affirmation and high praise.

293
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:45,400
Now, please welcome Secretary Peng to speak.

294
00:17:50,320 --> 00:17:51,120
Comrades,

295
00:17:51,520 --> 00:17:54,760
after the negative impact occurred this time,

296
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,560
our town's leadership team

297
00:17:56,560 --> 00:17:58,360
responded swiftly.

298
00:17:58,360 --> 00:18:01,760
Think about it, from deciding to hold the contest

299
00:18:01,760 --> 00:18:04,160
to its successful conclusion,

300
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:07,280
we only took half a month.

301
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:09,160
Half a month!

302
00:18:10,640 --> 00:18:13,480
About a hundred people participated, right?

303
00:18:13,480 --> 00:18:14,240
Yes.

304
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:16,920
Transport, food and lodging for so many,

305
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:20,360
safety, publicity, every little detail,

306
00:18:20,520 --> 00:18:22,920
our Lin Yiran and her teammates

307
00:18:23,120 --> 00:18:24,280
did a great job.

308
00:18:24,280 --> 00:18:26,800
And judging from the results,

309
00:18:27,080 --> 00:18:28,560
they pulled it off beautifully.

310
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:30,720
Director Liao,

311
00:18:31,480 --> 00:18:32,680
if this had been in the past,

312
00:18:33,560 --> 00:18:34,680
it wouldn't have been likely, right?

313
00:18:39,000 --> 00:18:39,800
Secretary Peng,

314
00:18:40,560 --> 00:18:41,520
fellow leaders,

315
00:18:42,080 --> 00:18:43,480
the Jiang Erhu cheating incident

316
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:45,440
that happened at this Paper King Competition

317
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:46,800
is my responsibility.

318
00:18:47,160 --> 00:18:48,520
I offer my self-criticism before this meeting.

319
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:50,240
That's a fairly proper attitude.

320
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:53,080
Lin Yiran, sit down.

321
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:54,480
Sit down.

322
00:18:56,480 --> 00:18:57,200
Of course,

323
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:59,840
throughout the entire competition process,

324
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:01,560
some problems did indeed arise.

325
00:19:01,840 --> 00:19:03,520
I think in this matter,

326
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:05,040
I also bear responsibility.

327
00:19:05,320 --> 00:19:08,520
But what I want to tell everyone today,

328
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:10,560
some comrades may not yet know:

329
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:14,040
Before the Paper King Competition began,

330
00:19:14,960 --> 00:19:16,680
this young woman Lin Yiran

331
00:19:17,240 --> 00:19:19,440
made a solemn pledge to me.

332
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:21,440
I'm deeply moved.

333
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:23,240
I was thinking,

334
00:19:23,840 --> 00:19:27,480
if every one of our officials

335
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:31,440
could shoulder this kind of responsibility,

336
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:35,080
what work could we possibly fail to do well?

337
00:19:35,560 --> 00:19:36,320
Good.

338
00:19:57,240 --> 00:19:57,960
You know what,

339
00:19:58,280 --> 00:20:00,680
I should find time to visit the Xuan family.

340
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:04,520
Master Xuan got played by Erhu.

341
00:20:04,760 --> 00:20:06,000
He didn't win the championship.

342
00:20:06,280 --> 00:20:07,240
I'm partly to blame too.

343
00:20:07,240 --> 00:20:07,840
Xiao Lin.

344
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:11,080
Hey, Xiao Lin.

345
00:20:11,400 --> 00:20:13,200
Wait, I mean Yiran.

346
00:20:13,560 --> 00:20:14,400
Yiran.

347
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:16,760
I remember you wrote something on

348
00:20:16,760 --> 00:20:18,880
the "Reporting System for Above-Scale Enterprises,"

349
00:20:18,880 --> 00:20:19,920
that report, right?

350
00:20:20,480 --> 00:20:21,280
Yes, I did.

351
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:22,280
I sent it to you,

352
00:20:22,280 --> 00:20:24,080
and also to Director Ge.

353
00:20:24,080 --> 00:20:24,960
Right, right, no worries.

354
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:26,600
When you have time, send me the digital copy.

355
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:27,560
If it's inconvenient, though—

356
00:20:27,560 --> 00:20:28,240
No, no, no.

357
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:29,320
It's fine, totally fine.

358
00:20:29,320 --> 00:20:30,320
I'll send it to you shortly.

359
00:20:30,320 --> 00:20:30,840
Alright, alright.

360
00:20:30,840 --> 00:20:31,640
Thanks for the trouble then.

361
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:32,840
One more thing.

362
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:35,040
The dynamic monitoring of poverty relapse,

363
00:20:35,040 --> 00:20:36,920
and the survey of key individuals,

364
00:20:36,920 --> 00:20:39,800
coordinate well with the village officials.

365
00:20:39,800 --> 00:20:40,600
Get on it quickly.

366
00:20:40,920 --> 00:20:42,440
The home visits for key individuals,

367
00:20:42,600 --> 00:20:44,400
not a single household can be missed.

368
00:20:45,040 --> 00:20:46,000
Especially the ones flagged

369
00:20:46,000 --> 00:20:48,160
by warnings from higher authorities.

370
00:20:48,680 --> 00:20:50,400
Not only must visits be thorough,

371
00:20:50,400 --> 00:20:51,760
but we also need concrete plans.

372
00:20:51,760 --> 00:20:52,760
That way we can promptly

373
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:54,600
report back to our superiors, right?

374
00:20:55,040 --> 00:20:55,840
Okay.

375
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:57,240
Alright, get back to work then.

376
00:20:57,760 --> 00:20:58,440
I'll head off now.

377
00:20:58,440 --> 00:21:00,000
Bye, bye, bye.

378
00:21:00,120 --> 00:21:01,000
Goodbye, Mayor.

379
00:21:04,480 --> 00:21:05,240
Wait

380
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:07,880
Is Deputy Mayor Luo really this polite?

381
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:10,160
First "Xiao Lin," then "Yiran."

382
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:12,360
Is there a difference?

383
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:15,120
He's polite to you

384
00:21:15,120 --> 00:21:16,480
because he's afraid you'll snap at him.

385
00:21:16,920 --> 00:21:18,360
You snap at everyone, top to bottom.

386
00:21:18,360 --> 00:21:19,280
Who wouldn't be afraid?

387
00:21:19,560 --> 00:21:20,640
The leaders are even more scared.

388
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:23,560
Terrified one word might set you off,

389
00:21:24,080 --> 00:21:25,600
and you'd embarrass them in public.

390
00:21:27,080 --> 00:21:29,800
Is that really how people see me?

391
00:21:31,520 --> 00:21:32,440
And quite vividly, too.

392
00:21:32,440 --> 00:21:33,480
You, right now,

393
00:21:33,480 --> 00:21:35,480
among all the officials in town,

394
00:21:35,520 --> 00:21:37,800
have a widely known nickname.

395
00:21:37,800 --> 00:21:39,680
"Snappy Lin."

396
00:21:40,840 --> 00:21:41,680
Me?

397
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:45,080
Oh my god.

398
00:21:46,720 --> 00:21:47,520
Uncle Xuan.

399
00:21:47,600 --> 00:21:48,600
Here, try this.

400
00:21:49,280 --> 00:21:51,800
It's a back massager I bought for you.

401
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:52,520
Here.

402
00:21:55,720 --> 00:21:56,320
What?

403
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:57,400
What is it?

404
00:21:57,400 --> 00:21:58,520
It's, it's moving around like that.

405
00:22:01,720 --> 00:22:03,600
This thing's way too fancy.

406
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:06,240
Xiao Lin, we can't accept this.

407
00:22:06,520 --> 00:22:08,760
You must. I bought it myself.

408
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:10,400
If you don't accept it,

409
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:11,880
I'll really feel hurt.

410
00:22:12,640 --> 00:22:14,400
Uncle Xuan, your craftsmanship is so good,

411
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:15,760
but you didn't win Paper King.

412
00:22:16,160 --> 00:22:17,560
That was a failure on my part.

413
00:22:17,560 --> 00:22:18,680
It's my responsibility.

414
00:22:19,080 --> 00:22:20,400
Don't ever think that way.

415
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:21,160
Come, come, come.

416
00:22:21,160 --> 00:22:22,080
Sit down, sit down.

417
00:22:22,400 --> 00:22:25,000
Don't take it to heart.

418
00:22:25,240 --> 00:22:26,600
The way things are done these days,

419
00:22:26,600 --> 00:22:28,960
plenty of folks don't play by the rules.

420
00:22:28,960 --> 00:22:30,240
They've got their own little schemes,

421
00:22:30,240 --> 00:22:32,000
pulling tricks here and there.

422
00:22:32,440 --> 00:22:33,760
That's all pretty common.

423
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:34,920
It's got nothing to do with you.

424
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:37,160
Don't gossip about others.

425
00:22:38,120 --> 00:22:39,280
Am I wrong, though?

426
00:22:39,360 --> 00:22:41,640
A few years back, the association met

427
00:22:41,640 --> 00:22:44,520
saying we'd resist unfair competition,

428
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:47,560
standardize paper quality and prices.

429
00:22:47,840 --> 00:22:48,680
And what happened?

430
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:51,040
Only our family actually did it.

431
00:22:51,040 --> 00:22:53,280
Others either cut corners,

432
00:22:53,280 --> 00:22:54,800
or sold at low prices,

433
00:22:55,440 --> 00:22:58,320
and just like that, we lost our customers.

434
00:22:58,520 --> 00:23:00,000
This guy in our family,

435
00:23:00,160 --> 00:23:01,840
all he knows is work, work, work,

436
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:03,080
never bothers to look at the road ahead.

437
00:23:03,080 --> 00:23:04,720
The Xuan family has come this far,

438
00:23:05,240 --> 00:23:06,800
thirty-five generations,

439
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:10,320
we've walked over a thousand years.

440
00:23:10,320 --> 00:23:11,720
Why would I need to look at the road?

441
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:14,520
Look too much, overthink it,

442
00:23:14,520 --> 00:23:16,640
and your steps will only stumble.

443
00:23:16,680 --> 00:23:18,160
That's exactly what I mean.

444
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:20,920
You're hanging yourself on one tree,

445
00:23:20,920 --> 00:23:22,720
and you still think you're so capable.

446
00:23:23,760 --> 00:23:24,680
Uncle Xuan,

447
00:23:25,160 --> 00:23:27,040
I feel your mindset

448
00:23:27,080 --> 00:23:29,400
is just like fine Xuan paper,

449
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:32,200
soft yet resilient, pure white as jade.

450
00:23:32,760 --> 00:23:35,280
Why not say he's stubborn and pig-headed?

451
00:23:39,080 --> 00:23:39,800
Xiao Lin,

452
00:23:40,360 --> 00:23:43,480
let me show you some prime Xuan paper.

453
00:23:43,880 --> 00:23:45,160
Are you interested?

454
00:23:45,920 --> 00:23:47,280
That'd be wonderful!

455
00:23:51,560 --> 00:23:53,160
Careful, it's dark in here.

456
00:23:54,320 --> 00:23:55,480
You go slow too, Uncle Xuan.

457
00:23:57,280 --> 00:23:58,080
After you.

458
00:24:10,760 --> 00:24:14,480
This was used for ancient imperial exams.

459
00:24:16,160 --> 00:24:20,280
This is for ministers' memorials to the throne.

460
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:21,800
And also,

461
00:24:23,200 --> 00:24:25,480
the emperor used this paper

462
00:24:26,120 --> 00:24:27,400
to make imperial decrees.

463
00:24:28,360 --> 00:24:29,560
All of these

464
00:24:30,320 --> 00:24:32,760
were made with our Xuan family's Xuan paper.

465
00:24:32,960 --> 00:24:35,400
So your paper was tribute paper, then.

466
00:24:35,760 --> 00:24:36,840
You could put it that way.

467
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:39,120
Since our Xuan family's first ancestor,

468
00:24:39,320 --> 00:24:42,400
we've sent tribute paper to the court.

469
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:43,920
Later, Beijing's Songhe Zhai

470
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:45,560
bought paper from our Xuan family,

471
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:49,200
used it for memorials and exam papers,

472
00:24:49,640 --> 00:24:50,720
and presented them to the court.

473
00:24:50,840 --> 00:24:52,880
I know Beijing's Songhe Zhai.

474
00:24:52,880 --> 00:24:54,680
A century-old brand, very famous.

475
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:55,840
Indeed, indeed.

476
00:24:59,440 --> 00:25:00,320
Take a look.

477
00:25:02,080 --> 00:25:03,400
This kind of Xuan paper—

478
00:25:03,640 --> 00:25:06,760
Republic-era presidential appointment letters,

479
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:09,520
and several of his presidential orders,

480
00:25:10,080 --> 00:25:11,960
were all made with this Xuan paper.

481
00:25:12,040 --> 00:25:15,080
These are treasures that have witnessed history.

482
00:25:17,240 --> 00:25:18,200
As for these three types,

483
00:25:18,200 --> 00:25:21,000
they're our Mianliao, Jingpi, and Tejingpi.

484
00:25:21,160 --> 00:25:23,000
You masters can try them out first.

485
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:23,600
See how they feel.

486
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:24,800
If you find they're not suitable,

487
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:26,600
we can also do custom orders.

488
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:27,680
Raw Xuan, processed Xuan,

489
00:25:27,680 --> 00:25:29,200
single-layer, double-layer—we make them all.

490
00:25:31,960 --> 00:25:32,760
Masters,

491
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:33,920
about our family's paper—

492
00:25:33,920 --> 00:25:36,440
Mianliao suits calligraphy and fine-brush painting.

493
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:39,400
Jingpi and Tejingpi suit freehand landscapes.

494
00:25:40,040 --> 00:25:41,080
They're all masters here.

495
00:25:41,520 --> 00:25:44,760
Lecturing them on basics is just embarrassing.

496
00:25:46,800 --> 00:25:47,600
Mr. Xiao.

497
00:25:51,960 --> 00:25:53,840
Go ahead and try it first.

498
00:25:57,360 --> 00:25:59,720
Your Jingpi and Tejingpi,

499
00:25:59,920 --> 00:26:01,040
what's the wholesale price?

500
00:26:04,600 --> 00:26:07,280
Where did you buy from before?

501
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:08,080
The Xuan family.

502
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:12,680
Then why come to me now?

503
00:26:13,280 --> 00:26:14,280
To be honest with you,

504
00:26:14,520 --> 00:26:16,440
we've always sold high-end goods,

505
00:26:16,520 --> 00:26:17,560
collector-grade paper.

506
00:26:17,840 --> 00:26:19,480
Give us a better price,

507
00:26:19,560 --> 00:26:20,720
and we'll do business with you.

508
00:26:21,320 --> 00:26:22,720
I'll be honest with you too.

509
00:26:23,120 --> 00:26:25,400
My paper isn't collector-grade.

510
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:27,080
A big paper mill boss like you,

511
00:26:27,080 --> 00:26:28,520
talking like an outsider.

512
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:30,520
Good paper gets pricier with age.

513
00:26:30,920 --> 00:26:34,280
Who actually paints on collector paper?

514
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:35,520
Mr. Xiao,

515
00:26:35,720 --> 00:26:37,920
you're the Paper King now.

516
00:26:38,760 --> 00:26:40,680
Honestly speaking,

517
00:26:41,040 --> 00:26:42,160
the Xuan family's paper

518
00:26:42,720 --> 00:26:43,720
is way too expensive.

519
00:26:43,840 --> 00:26:45,760
I'm buying your Paper King reputation.

520
00:26:46,120 --> 00:26:48,240
It'll move well in the market.

521
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:48,960
Exactly.

522
00:26:49,120 --> 00:26:50,160
Mutual benefit.

523
00:26:50,240 --> 00:26:52,480
Everyone makes money. Isn't that great?

524
00:26:52,840 --> 00:26:53,680
Yes, yes, yes.

525
00:26:54,360 --> 00:26:55,720
Mutual benefit

526
00:26:55,880 --> 00:26:57,080
is definitely a good thing.

527
00:26:57,440 --> 00:26:59,760
Who doesn't want to earn more these days?

528
00:26:59,760 --> 00:27:01,720
But my Paper King title is fake.

529
00:27:03,680 --> 00:27:04,840
In our Taohua Town,

530
00:27:05,520 --> 00:27:07,080
only the Xuan family

531
00:27:07,240 --> 00:27:08,400
sells collector-grade paper.

532
00:27:09,240 --> 00:27:11,800
We have to do business with integrity.

533
00:27:11,840 --> 00:27:12,640
Right?

534
00:27:16,120 --> 00:27:16,960
Gentlemen,

535
00:27:17,920 --> 00:27:18,800
how was the test?

536
00:27:19,920 --> 00:27:21,120
These two buyers

537
00:27:21,480 --> 00:27:24,360
used to buy paper from my master, the Xuans.

538
00:27:24,360 --> 00:27:26,440
Today they came specifically to me.

539
00:27:26,440 --> 00:27:29,600
Please give your honest opinions, gentlemen,

540
00:27:29,600 --> 00:27:31,280
on how my paper is.

541
00:27:31,440 --> 00:27:33,000
This Jingpi of yours,

542
00:27:33,800 --> 00:27:37,480
the ink spread doesn't feel smooth enough.

543
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:39,160
Its ink absorption

544
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:42,200
seems a bit lacking.

545
00:27:42,400 --> 00:27:43,400
I'm certain

546
00:27:44,160 --> 00:27:45,440
the sandalwood bark content

547
00:27:46,320 --> 00:27:48,640
definitely doesn't exceed 60 percent.

548
00:27:48,840 --> 00:27:50,520
What's my philosophy on choosing paper?

549
00:27:51,440 --> 00:27:54,000
Choose by spirit, not by form.

550
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:55,680
What do you mean?

551
00:27:58,800 --> 00:28:00,800
Many calligraphers and painters say,

552
00:28:00,960 --> 00:28:04,720
"I pick raw, sized, or semi-sized Xuan,

553
00:28:05,040 --> 00:28:08,280
whatever suits me, what I can master."

554
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:11,080
I think that view is wrong.

555
00:28:11,760 --> 00:28:12,920
If you've mastered it,

556
00:28:13,360 --> 00:28:14,960
how can the paper's spirit emerge?

557
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:18,040
I believe it's not mastery,

558
00:28:18,320 --> 00:28:20,360
it's interaction.

559
00:28:20,600 --> 00:28:22,200
Interaction is best.

560
00:28:22,440 --> 00:28:25,800
Didn't you just say "spirit, not form"?

561
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:31,600
Sorry, sorry.

562
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:32,800
I forgot to introduce him.

563
00:28:33,480 --> 00:28:35,640
Allow me to formally introduce

564
00:28:36,120 --> 00:28:37,480
Director Liao Shanming.

565
00:28:37,960 --> 00:28:39,360
He is our Taohua Town's

566
00:28:39,520 --> 00:28:42,160
renowned Xuan paper theory expert.

567
00:28:42,600 --> 00:28:44,520
His research on Xuan paper theory

568
00:28:44,520 --> 00:28:45,800
runs very deep.

569
00:28:46,480 --> 00:28:47,800
Don't rush, everyone.

570
00:28:48,080 --> 00:28:49,840
Let me explain slowly.

571
00:28:51,160 --> 00:28:55,680
Interaction ties right into choosing by spirit.

572
00:28:55,920 --> 00:28:57,040
For example,

573
00:28:57,400 --> 00:28:58,440
Qi Baishi

574
00:28:59,040 --> 00:29:02,440
focused on precise brushstroke expression,

575
00:29:02,480 --> 00:29:04,680
while Huang Zhou needed

576
00:29:04,720 --> 00:29:06,960
Jingpi and Tejingpi to support

577
00:29:06,960 --> 00:29:08,960
his sweeping creative energy.

578
00:29:09,560 --> 00:29:11,240
The brush follows the heart,

579
00:29:11,480 --> 00:29:13,240
the heart follows the ink,

580
00:29:13,320 --> 00:29:16,320
and how the ink moves depends on the paper.

581
00:29:22,440 --> 00:29:22,920
Thank you.

582
00:29:36,520 --> 00:29:37,200
What?

583
00:29:37,200 --> 00:29:38,080
Where's my bag?

584
00:29:38,720 --> 00:29:39,400
What bag?

585
00:29:40,400 --> 00:29:41,480
The bag and the water bottle!

586
00:29:47,560 --> 00:29:48,240
Sir!

587
00:29:48,240 --> 00:29:49,440
Director Liao! Director Liao!

588
00:29:49,440 --> 00:29:50,240
We can't catch up.

589
00:29:51,760 --> 00:29:52,400
This...

590
00:29:53,200 --> 00:29:54,240
I... I have a scooter.

591
00:29:54,240 --> 00:29:54,840
I have a scooter, I have one!

592
00:29:54,840 --> 00:29:55,400
Okay, let's go!

593
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:55,840
I have a scooter.

594
00:29:55,840 --> 00:29:56,520
Hurry!

595
00:30:04,600 --> 00:30:06,240
Wait, can we even catch up?

596
00:30:06,920 --> 00:30:08,200
We have to try anyway.

597
00:30:16,960 --> 00:30:18,800
This whole thing just shows

598
00:30:19,240 --> 00:30:21,440
you don't take your boss seriously at all.

599
00:30:22,320 --> 00:30:24,480
Sorry. If it's lost, I'll pay for it.

600
00:30:25,800 --> 00:30:26,960
This isn't about paying me back.

601
00:30:27,520 --> 00:30:28,760
It's about your attitude.

602
00:30:29,320 --> 00:30:30,440
With an attitude like yours,

603
00:30:30,520 --> 00:30:32,720
it's clear you have no "drive."

604
00:30:33,240 --> 00:30:34,040
What drive?

605
00:30:34,800 --> 00:30:35,600
What drive?

606
00:30:35,960 --> 00:30:37,440
The drive to advance.

607
00:30:38,040 --> 00:30:39,480
Well, I don't care about that drive.

608
00:30:39,760 --> 00:30:40,600
What did you say?

609
00:30:41,400 --> 00:30:43,240
I just do my job well, that's enough.

610
00:30:43,240 --> 00:30:44,440
Whether I advance or not, I don't care.

611
00:30:45,080 --> 00:30:46,520
What do you mean you don't care?

612
00:30:48,240 --> 00:30:49,840
Don't follow Taozi's example, I'm telling you.

613
00:30:50,080 --> 00:30:51,440
You don't have her advantages.

614
00:30:52,080 --> 00:30:54,160
Fine. Thank you for the lecture, boss.

615
00:30:56,560 --> 00:30:57,760
Tell me the truth.

616
00:30:57,960 --> 00:30:59,040
Did you lose my bag

617
00:30:59,480 --> 00:31:00,600
on purpose?

618
00:31:01,200 --> 00:31:02,120
No, how could you say that?

619
00:31:02,120 --> 00:31:03,040
I didn't.

620
00:31:04,280 --> 00:31:05,040
Don't play games with me.

621
00:31:05,040 --> 00:31:05,800
I'm telling you,

622
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:07,400
I can see right through everything.

623
00:31:07,800 --> 00:31:09,160
I really didn't.

624
00:31:09,920 --> 00:31:10,880
Yeah, right.

625
00:31:18,720 --> 00:31:19,520
Excuse me, comrade.

626
00:31:19,920 --> 00:31:21,240
E-scooters aren't allowed to carry

627
00:31:21,240 --> 00:31:22,600
adults over sixteen years old.

628
00:31:22,600 --> 00:31:23,600
Didn't you know that?

629
00:31:24,120 --> 00:31:25,600
And you're not wearing a helmet.

630
00:31:25,880 --> 00:31:26,800
You have to accept the penalty.

631
00:31:33,760 --> 00:31:34,520
Sir!

632
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:36,200
This is the guy, right?

633
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:36,560
Yes, yes, yes!

634
00:31:36,560 --> 00:31:37,680
I... let me, let me!

635
00:31:38,080 --> 00:31:38,720
Sir.

636
00:31:38,720 --> 00:31:40,040
This is your bottle, right?

637
00:31:40,040 --> 00:31:40,520
Yes.

638
00:31:40,520 --> 00:31:41,160
The bag.

639
00:31:41,840 --> 00:31:42,760
Thank you so much, sir!

640
00:31:42,760 --> 00:31:43,200
No need, no need.

641
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:43,960
It's what anyone would do.

642
00:31:43,960 --> 00:31:45,240
Thank you, sir! Thank you, sir!

643
00:31:45,240 --> 00:31:46,000
Thank you so much, sir!

644
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:46,600
It's nothing, really.

645
00:31:46,600 --> 00:31:47,560
It's fine, it's fine.

646
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:48,600
Let me treat you to a meal.

647
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:49,520
No, no, no need.

648
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:50,440
I'm off.

649
00:31:50,440 --> 00:31:51,240
Thank you, sir!

650
00:31:51,400 --> 00:31:52,200
Thank you, sir!

651
00:31:58,520 --> 00:31:59,960
Look at his sense of duty.

652
00:32:08,520 --> 00:32:11,520
That Manager Hu who used to order paper from us

653
00:32:12,560 --> 00:32:14,440
ran off to order from old Ren's place.

654
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:16,320
Don't talk nonsense.

655
00:32:16,440 --> 00:32:17,440
Who's talking nonsense?

656
00:32:17,680 --> 00:32:19,840
I saw it with my own eyes!

657
00:32:20,080 --> 00:32:22,520
This time, Xiao Yu really isn't making it up.

658
00:32:22,800 --> 00:32:24,080
At this Paper King Contest,

659
00:32:24,080 --> 00:32:26,000
over thirty buyers showed up.

660
00:32:26,000 --> 00:32:28,040
Seven or eight of them were familiar faces.

661
00:32:28,040 --> 00:32:30,400
They all used to order from the Xuan family.

662
00:32:30,480 --> 00:32:31,960
After we lost the contest,

663
00:32:32,560 --> 00:32:33,840
not a single one showed up.

664
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:35,520
These people are such opportunists.

665
00:32:35,520 --> 00:32:36,720
Just shut up already.

666
00:32:36,760 --> 00:32:37,960
Enough of your nonsense.

667
00:32:37,960 --> 00:32:39,160
Go haul your paperboards.

668
00:32:39,720 --> 00:32:41,040
I'm just worried, that's all.

669
00:32:41,040 --> 00:32:42,320
I'm just saying.

670
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:44,200
We've got wages this month,

671
00:32:44,600 --> 00:32:46,760
but next month is anyone's guess.

672
00:32:54,400 --> 00:32:56,680
The Calligraphy Association's payment still hasn't come in.

673
00:32:57,040 --> 00:32:58,240
Have you checked?

674
00:32:58,240 --> 00:32:59,520
Of course I checked.

675
00:32:59,600 --> 00:33:00,600
I checked yesterday,

676
00:33:00,600 --> 00:33:01,680
and I checked again today.

677
00:33:01,680 --> 00:33:02,400
Nothing's come in.

678
00:33:03,160 --> 00:33:04,680
Which account did you check?

679
00:33:05,520 --> 00:33:07,240
How many accounts do we even have?

680
00:33:07,240 --> 00:33:08,600
Just this one.

681
00:33:11,240 --> 00:33:12,560
I checked the shipping too.

682
00:33:12,720 --> 00:33:15,000
They received the goods a week ago.

683
00:33:16,840 --> 00:33:18,240
They wouldn't stiff us, would they?

684
00:33:18,960 --> 00:33:21,200
Old Sun's worked with us for decades.

685
00:33:21,760 --> 00:33:23,840
He shouldn't pull something like that.

686
00:33:24,000 --> 00:33:25,400
Let's wait a bit longer.

687
00:33:26,200 --> 00:33:28,440
Maybe it'll come in tonight.

688
00:33:29,320 --> 00:33:30,080
This morning,

689
00:33:30,080 --> 00:33:32,400
the workers were already talking about wages.

690
00:33:32,480 --> 00:33:34,760
They all know payday is today.

691
00:33:36,240 --> 00:33:37,080
They're waiting.

692
00:33:39,520 --> 00:33:40,320
Hard at work.

693
00:33:40,760 --> 00:33:41,720
Brother Xuan Yi.

694
00:33:41,720 --> 00:33:42,320
Xuan Yi.

695
00:33:42,320 --> 00:33:43,120
Uncle Ye.

696
00:33:44,080 --> 00:33:44,600
Xuan Yi.

697
00:33:44,600 --> 00:33:45,200
Uncle.

698
00:33:46,080 --> 00:33:47,280
What are you doing, Zhang Du?

699
00:33:47,720 --> 00:33:50,600
You don't need a whole ritual just to scoop paper.

700
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:52,600
Paper-scooping is paid by the piece.

701
00:33:52,800 --> 00:33:55,000
If Uncle Ye's family all worked like you,

702
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:56,080
they'd have starved long ago.

703
00:33:57,240 --> 00:34:00,760
Scooping paper and scooping good paper are two different things.

704
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:03,080
Xiao Man, did you hear that?

705
00:34:03,440 --> 00:34:05,760
You'd better help the master scoop it properly.

706
00:34:05,760 --> 00:34:06,960
It's got to be good paper.

707
00:34:07,920 --> 00:34:10,040
He thinks I'm too dim-witted,

708
00:34:10,040 --> 00:34:11,040
beyond hope of mastering this.

709
00:34:11,320 --> 00:34:13,239
You're just not devoted enough. Look at him.

710
00:34:14,320 --> 00:34:15,120
Brother Yi.

711
00:34:16,199 --> 00:34:17,520
We're getting paid today, right?

712
00:34:17,960 --> 00:34:19,760
Beanpole, what are you on about?

713
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:23,480
The exact time isn't clear yet,

714
00:34:23,760 --> 00:34:24,719
but my mom was already

715
00:34:24,719 --> 00:34:26,480
sorting through pay slips last night.

716
00:34:26,600 --> 00:34:28,920
I'd say within a day or two.

717
00:34:29,199 --> 00:34:30,000
Got it.

718
00:34:30,719 --> 00:34:31,520
Got it.

719
00:34:51,760 --> 00:34:53,000
Is this guy nuts?

720
00:34:53,400 --> 00:34:54,199
Who's that?

721
00:34:56,199 --> 00:34:57,720
Hey, hey!

722
00:34:58,240 --> 00:34:59,720
What are you doing?

723
00:34:59,720 --> 00:35:00,760
Stop, stop!

724
00:35:01,080 --> 00:35:01,760
What's going on?

725
00:35:01,760 --> 00:35:02,680
What are you people doing?

726
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:04,000
You think this is your house?

727
00:35:04,200 --> 00:35:05,000
Honking the horn like crazy.

728
00:35:05,000 --> 00:35:05,840
Returning the goods.

729
00:35:05,840 --> 00:35:07,000
Returning what goods?

730
00:35:07,720 --> 00:35:08,800
A return is a return.

731
00:35:09,240 --> 00:35:10,280
Meaning all the goods you shipped

732
00:35:10,280 --> 00:35:11,840
have been sent back, untouched.

733
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:12,920
Get it now?

734
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:15,520
This time, wages really can't be paid.

735
00:35:16,400 --> 00:35:17,200
Old Xuan.

736
00:35:18,760 --> 00:35:19,520
Old Xuan.

737
00:35:20,360 --> 00:35:21,520
You've heard already, right?

738
00:35:22,040 --> 00:35:22,560
Heard what?

739
00:35:24,040 --> 00:35:25,840
They just refuse it, just like that.

740
00:35:25,840 --> 00:35:27,760
We put in so much cost.

741
00:35:27,760 --> 00:35:29,920
A whole crew worked for a month.

742
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:31,480
Where's the sense in that?

743
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:35,040
Don't get worked up.

744
00:35:35,040 --> 00:35:36,600
They bought my paper

745
00:35:36,840 --> 00:35:40,080
for investment and collection.

746
00:35:40,480 --> 00:35:41,920
Now that the Paper King title is gone,

747
00:35:42,040 --> 00:35:43,920
the investment and collection value

748
00:35:44,160 --> 00:35:45,640
has taken a hit.

749
00:35:46,840 --> 00:35:48,360
Even if you're not the Paper King,

750
00:35:48,360 --> 00:35:50,480
you're still an intangible heritage inheritor.

751
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:51,040
Right?

752
00:35:51,040 --> 00:35:52,760
You lose one competition,

753
00:35:52,760 --> 00:35:54,360
and they bail on the order?

754
00:35:54,360 --> 00:35:55,760
We've already paid the costs.

755
00:35:55,760 --> 00:35:57,720
They still owe us the money.

756
00:35:57,840 --> 00:35:58,640
Forget it.

757
00:35:59,120 --> 00:36:00,240
You can lead an ox to water,

758
00:36:00,240 --> 00:36:01,640
but you can't force its head down.

759
00:36:03,520 --> 00:36:04,880
That's just how it is.

760
00:36:05,120 --> 00:36:07,360
When they want paper, they sweet-talk you.

761
00:36:07,360 --> 00:36:08,640
When they don't want it,

762
00:36:08,680 --> 00:36:10,440
they sweet-talk you all the same.

763
00:36:10,560 --> 00:36:11,600
These people...

764
00:36:11,600 --> 00:36:12,920
Once they get the goods,

765
00:36:13,800 --> 00:36:15,200
they stop paying.

766
00:36:15,440 --> 00:36:17,200
Try chasing them for money,

767
00:36:17,920 --> 00:36:20,680
and they act like we owe them.

768
00:36:22,200 --> 00:36:24,080
So now you finally figured it out?

769
00:36:24,400 --> 00:36:25,640
Back then, I told them

770
00:36:25,640 --> 00:36:26,960
they had to pay a deposit.

771
00:36:26,960 --> 00:36:28,880
And you said, "No need, no need, no need."

772
00:36:28,880 --> 00:36:30,040
"It's fine."

773
00:36:30,160 --> 00:36:30,960
Well, look at us now.

774
00:36:30,960 --> 00:36:32,280
The money's not coming in,

775
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:33,520
wages can't be paid.

776
00:36:33,720 --> 00:36:34,840
You figure it out yourself.

777
00:36:37,440 --> 00:36:40,200
The orders are still coming in, aren't they?

778
00:36:40,680 --> 00:36:41,880
They haven't stopped, right?

779
00:36:42,680 --> 00:36:44,440
I'm telling you, you're really something.

780
00:36:44,480 --> 00:36:45,560
You only think about the income,

781
00:36:45,560 --> 00:36:46,640
not the expenses.

782
00:36:46,920 --> 00:36:48,480
Let me do the math for you.

783
00:36:49,160 --> 00:36:50,360
Our workers,

784
00:36:50,360 --> 00:36:52,920
they earn the highest wages in town, right?

785
00:36:53,360 --> 00:36:55,840
The social security and insurance we provide,

786
00:36:55,840 --> 00:36:57,360
isn't that also the highest standard?

787
00:36:57,440 --> 00:36:58,680
Other factories,

788
00:36:58,680 --> 00:37:00,000
when business is slow,

789
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:01,600
they just lay the workers off.

790
00:37:01,600 --> 00:37:02,760
But us, oh no,

791
00:37:02,960 --> 00:37:04,280
slow season, busy season,

792
00:37:04,280 --> 00:37:05,960
we keep paying the workers.

793
00:37:06,080 --> 00:37:07,240
And the drying yard,

794
00:37:07,240 --> 00:37:09,520
don't we have to manage all that too?

795
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,600
Making the bleached bark ourselves,

796
00:37:11,600 --> 00:37:13,520
how high is that cost?

797
00:37:13,640 --> 00:37:15,520
You've never done the math on any of this.

798
00:37:15,720 --> 00:37:18,000
You're selling tofu at the price of meat.

799
00:37:18,240 --> 00:37:20,000
Being generous when you're broke,

800
00:37:20,040 --> 00:37:21,520
that's exactly the kind of person you are.

801
00:37:22,760 --> 00:37:23,560
Come in.

802
00:37:25,440 --> 00:37:26,680
Master, Madam.

803
00:37:27,160 --> 00:37:28,800
Uncle Lao Cheng, the straw maker, is here.

804
00:37:28,800 --> 00:37:30,080
I told him you were sick,

805
00:37:30,200 --> 00:37:32,800
but he said he came just to see you.

806
00:37:32,880 --> 00:37:34,520
This... this is...

807
00:37:34,800 --> 00:37:36,040
He came to ask for money.

808
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:38,080
Here's the thing.

809
00:37:39,200 --> 00:37:41,200
My second daughter, Shanqin,

810
00:37:41,720 --> 00:37:43,880
she's busy with work in the provincial capital.

811
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:47,560
She blames us for not helping raise her child.

812
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:50,680
Every single time she comes back,

813
00:37:50,680 --> 00:37:52,520
she gets upset every time.

814
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:54,320
Our eldest daughter's child,

815
00:37:54,320 --> 00:37:55,960
the two of us raised her.

816
00:37:56,640 --> 00:37:57,600
But the second one,

817
00:37:59,160 --> 00:38:00,160
we didn't help take care of hers,

818
00:38:00,200 --> 00:38:02,200
so she's been holding a grudge.

819
00:38:04,320 --> 00:38:07,000
So the two of us have been thinking,

820
00:38:07,520 --> 00:38:10,560
maybe we should just move to the city.

821
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:12,920
But if we do that,

822
00:38:13,840 --> 00:38:15,480
next year, the bleached straw,

823
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:19,720
we won't be able to make it anymore.

824
00:38:20,880 --> 00:38:22,720
After all these decades of friendship,

825
00:38:23,720 --> 00:38:25,080
I... these words, I...

826
00:38:25,280 --> 00:38:27,480
I really don't know how to say it.

827
00:38:35,200 --> 00:38:36,000
Xiumei

828
00:38:36,520 --> 00:38:37,440
Go check

829
00:38:38,520 --> 00:38:40,520
how much we've got left in the account

830
00:38:40,600 --> 00:38:42,160
Forget everything else for now

831
00:38:42,320 --> 00:38:45,280
Scrape together what we owe Lao Cheng first

832
00:38:45,560 --> 00:38:46,960
Lao Xuan, this...

833
00:38:46,960 --> 00:38:47,680
Just go

834
00:38:53,120 --> 00:38:54,440
This is so embarrassing

835
00:38:54,880 --> 00:38:55,680
It's fine

836
00:38:58,960 --> 00:38:59,720
Sister Xu

837
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:00,680
Busy, huh?

838
00:39:00,800 --> 00:39:01,560
Look at this pork

839
00:39:01,560 --> 00:39:02,680
How much is the pork today?

840
00:39:02,680 --> 00:39:04,120
Today, eighteen a jin

841
00:39:04,480 --> 00:39:07,080
The price keeps going up day by day

842
00:39:07,400 --> 00:39:07,880
Give me a discount

843
00:39:08,520 --> 00:39:10,480
Cheaper, I'm a regular

844
00:39:10,800 --> 00:39:11,520
Sixteen

845
00:39:11,520 --> 00:39:13,320
I'll take all three chunks for sixteen

846
00:39:13,320 --> 00:39:13,720
Deal

847
00:39:13,720 --> 00:39:14,200
Okay, okay

848
00:39:14,200 --> 00:39:14,600
Go weigh it

849
00:39:14,600 --> 00:39:15,520
Alright, alright

850
00:39:18,480 --> 00:39:19,000
Mom

851
00:39:19,600 --> 00:39:21,640
Haggling over a dime or a buck

852
00:39:22,080 --> 00:39:23,320
is it really worth the fuss?

853
00:39:23,320 --> 00:39:24,320
They have it tough too

854
00:39:24,720 --> 00:39:25,840
I have it tough myself

855
00:39:25,880 --> 00:39:26,640
Save where you can

856
00:39:29,040 --> 00:39:30,360
How much per jin for tomatoes?

857
00:39:30,360 --> 00:39:30,880
Eighty cents

858
00:39:31,040 --> 00:39:31,800
Eighty cents?

859
00:39:31,840 --> 00:39:32,800
What's going on here?

860
00:39:32,840 --> 00:39:33,800
Tomatoes, eighty cents

861
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:34,120
Hold on

862
00:39:34,120 --> 00:39:35,800
What, do we have to fight for these?

863
00:39:35,880 --> 00:39:36,560
Come over here, quick

864
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:37,720
Come on, bag them up, hurry

865
00:39:37,760 --> 00:39:38,480
This stall is cheaper

866
00:39:38,480 --> 00:39:39,400
My hands are full, Mom

867
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:40,760
Put your stuff on the ground

868
00:39:40,760 --> 00:39:42,080
Hurry, grab a couple more bags

869
00:39:42,080 --> 00:39:42,960
Quick, his is cheaper

870
00:39:42,960 --> 00:39:44,200
We don't really need this many

871
00:39:44,960 --> 00:39:46,200
Big family, big appetite

872
00:39:46,200 --> 00:39:47,200
Don't pick the ones that are too...

873
00:39:47,280 --> 00:39:48,760
Don't shove, don't shove

874
00:39:49,480 --> 00:39:50,520
Don't pick the soft ones

875
00:39:50,520 --> 00:39:52,040
Get the slightly firmer ones

876
00:39:52,120 --> 00:39:52,880
Bag them up

877
00:39:52,880 --> 00:39:54,120
Bagging, bagging, I'm on it

878
00:39:54,560 --> 00:39:55,440
Oh my goodness

879
00:39:56,240 --> 00:39:58,000
Buying this much, we can't finish it, it's a waste

880
00:39:58,160 --> 00:39:58,880
Not a waste

881
00:39:58,880 --> 00:40:00,040
We've got lots of mouths to feed

882
00:40:00,040 --> 00:40:01,040
Don't worry

883
00:40:02,200 --> 00:40:04,080
Mom, you really know how to pinch a penny

884
00:40:04,400 --> 00:40:06,000
If I don't, who will?

885
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:08,080
Anyone who holds out their hand,

886
00:40:08,080 --> 00:40:09,520
your dad just hands it over

887
00:40:09,680 --> 00:40:11,040
So then I have to give too, right?

888
00:40:11,320 --> 00:40:12,000
Come on, come on

889
00:40:13,560 --> 00:40:15,480
If I weren't running this household,

890
00:40:16,200 --> 00:40:18,000
who knows if you'd even have made it this far

891
00:40:18,040 --> 00:40:19,240
Come on, Mom, it's not that bad

892
00:40:19,240 --> 00:40:20,480
What do you mean it's not that bad?

893
00:40:20,720 --> 00:40:22,840
From the daily groceries

894
00:40:22,880 --> 00:40:24,760
to the factory's books

895
00:40:24,760 --> 00:40:26,320
which part don't I have to worry about?

896
00:40:26,360 --> 00:40:27,320
Rely on your dad?

897
00:40:28,400 --> 00:40:28,920
Come on, come on

898
00:40:28,920 --> 00:40:30,560
If there's no money to pay wages,

899
00:40:31,360 --> 00:40:32,280
no money to keep things running,

900
00:40:32,280 --> 00:40:33,440
your dad comes running to me

901
00:40:33,440 --> 00:40:34,320
Rely on him?

902
00:40:36,560 --> 00:40:37,360
Mom

903
00:40:37,560 --> 00:40:38,680
Our paper scooping and drying

904
00:40:38,680 --> 00:40:40,080
is all piece-rate work

905
00:40:40,520 --> 00:40:41,520
Just scoop less

906
00:40:41,520 --> 00:40:42,720
and you save on everything

907
00:40:43,320 --> 00:40:44,720
Go tell your dad that

908
00:40:47,560 --> 00:40:49,080
Fish, half price!

909
00:41:11,720 --> 00:41:12,200
Dad.

910
00:41:12,400 --> 00:41:13,680
Mom's got dinner ready.

911
00:41:13,840 --> 00:41:14,600
Come down and eat.

912
00:41:24,520 --> 00:41:25,720
Mom said,

913
00:41:26,400 --> 00:41:28,040
we can't cover this month's wages.

914
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:29,480
She's at her wit's end,

915
00:41:30,000 --> 00:41:31,000
so she sent me over

916
00:41:31,360 --> 00:41:32,480
to talk it over with you.

917
00:41:42,720 --> 00:41:44,440
Do you have any good ideas?

918
00:41:45,560 --> 00:41:47,320
Well, since you're asking, I'll say it.

919
00:41:48,680 --> 00:41:49,840
It's not just my opinion,

920
00:41:50,280 --> 00:41:51,480
it's how business works.

921
00:41:52,280 --> 00:41:54,160
We're running a business, not a charity.

922
00:41:54,160 --> 00:41:54,880
Right?

923
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:56,760
If we can't pay the wages,

924
00:41:57,520 --> 00:41:59,160
we shut down one vat.

925
00:41:59,480 --> 00:42:00,520
And if that doesn't work,

926
00:42:00,600 --> 00:42:02,960
we just halt operations for a while.

927
00:42:03,480 --> 00:42:04,200
Look,

928
00:42:04,200 --> 00:42:05,880
we've still got this much paper in stock.

929
00:42:05,880 --> 00:42:09,000
Let's find a way to sell off the inventory first.

930
00:42:09,920 --> 00:42:11,200
What business in trouble

931
00:42:11,200 --> 00:42:13,120
doesn't cut its losses to survive?

932
00:42:14,520 --> 00:42:16,920
The business has to survive first,

933
00:42:17,240 --> 00:42:18,480
then the workers can put food on the table.

934
00:42:19,160 --> 00:42:21,880
That's how you secure their jobs.

935
00:42:22,120 --> 00:42:24,840
These are the basic rules of survival.

936
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:29,960
Our Xuan family ancestors

937
00:42:31,600 --> 00:42:33,440
laid down a rule like this:

938
00:42:33,640 --> 00:42:36,840
We can't just make money when times are good,

939
00:42:37,560 --> 00:42:39,440
then when next year turns bad,

940
00:42:40,720 --> 00:42:42,840
ignore whether the workers live or die

941
00:42:43,520 --> 00:42:45,600
and just kick them out.

942
00:42:46,400 --> 00:42:48,640
That breaks people's hearts.

943
00:42:49,960 --> 00:42:52,920
Later, if you want them back,

944
00:42:55,840 --> 00:42:58,120
it'll be extremely hard.
